What is your mywc program test plan?

Boundary tests:

mywc001.txt: This file has a normal line of words separated by spaces. It checks that the program can count a simple input correctly.

mywc002.txt: This file has words on multiple lines, but the last line does not end with a newline. It checks that the program does not overcount lines at EOF.

mywc003.txt: This file has only whitespace characters: spaces, tabs, and newlines. It checks that the program counts characters and lines, but counts zero words.

mywc004.txt: This file has one word and no trailing newline. It checks that the program still counts the word when EOF happens immediately after it.

Statement tests:

mywc001.txt: This file tests the normal word-counting path. It executes the main loop on lines 30-50, character counting on line 32, non-whitespace handling on lines 42-46, word entry on line 45, whitespace handling on lines 34-40, word counting on line 38, and final printing on lines 55-56.

mywc002.txt: This file tests words across lines. It executes the main loop on lines 30-50, character counting on line 32, word handling on lines 42-46, newline checking on line 48, line counting on line 49, the final word check on lines 52-53, and final printing on lines 55-56.

mywc003.txt: This file tests the whitespace-only case. It executes the main loop on lines 30-50, character counting on line 32, whitespace handling on lines 34-40, newline checking on line 48, line counting on line 49, and final printing on lines 55-56. It does not enter the non-whitespace word path.

mywc004.txt: This file tests a single word with no newline. It executes the main loop on lines 30-50, character counting on line 32, non-whitespace handling on lines 42-46, word entry on line 45, the final word check on lines 52-53, and final printing on lines 55-56.

mywc005.txt: This file has punctuation and mixed whitespace, including tabs. It executes both the whitespace path on lines 34-40 and the non-whitespace path on lines 42-46. It also checks that punctuation is counted as part of a word, since punctuation is not whitespace.

Stress tests:

mywc006.txt: This file has very long words and/or long lines. It stress tests the loop on lines 30-50 and makes sure character counting on line 32 still works for a large input.

mywc007.txt: This file has many repeated lines with many words. It stress tests repeated word transitions, newline counting on lines 48-49, and final output on lines 55-56.

